entities.entity:
<GROUND_RULES>
Use ONLY the explicit Q&A in the context. No assumptions.
If a field is not explicitly stated, output NULL.

OUTPUT EXACTLY 4 lines (no extra lines, no wrapping):
EE:
Sp:
Child:
Rehire:

Fragments only (no full sentences). Keep short.
Exclude: open enrollment/QLE, “making changes”, COBRA/HRA claims, coverage end/termination, contribution/participation/GI, other benefits.

FIELD RULES:
EE: hours/class + effective trigger (DOH / 90th day / 1st of month after X days). If one is missing, write the other; missing part = NULL.
Sp: spouse type only (legal spouse / domestic partner / common law) or NULL.
Child: child age limit only (to age 26 / EOM age 26 / etc.) or NULL.
Rehire: rehire/reinstatement threshold only (e.g., 90 days) or NULL.
</GROUND_RULES>

Eligibility Language Q&A:
<CONTEXT>
{{DR_MEligibilityLanguageQA}}
</CONTEXT>

<QUESTIONS>
Return the 4-line Eligibility output. <Answer>
</QUESTIONS>

<EXAMPLES>
EE: 30 hrs/week, effective 1st of month after 30 days
Sp: legal spouse or domestic partner
Child: to age 26
Rehire: NULL

EE: 35 hrs/week, effective 1st of month after 30 days
Sp: legal spouse
Child: to age 26
Rehire: 90 days
</EXAMPLES>

<GROUND_RULES>
Use ONLY the explicit Q&A in context. No assumptions.
If no explicit termination timing rule is stated, output Null.

OUTPUT:
- Only termination timing. Ignore COBRA/continuation, HRA, contacts/Marketplace.
- If no benefit split: output exactly 1 line:
  Coverage terminates <timing> <trigger>
- If benefit timing differs: output 1 line per unique timing:
  <BenefitGroup>: Coverage terminates <timing>
  Use SHORT labels and combine same-timing benefits with slashes (e.g., Med/Vis/Rx). No duplicate-timing lines.
No extra lines.

LABELS:
Use short benefit labels (capitalize): Med, Vis, Dtl, Rx, Hra, Fsa, Hsa, Std, Ltd, Life, etc. If doc uses different labels, map to closest.

NORMALIZE:
last day of the month -> end of month
end of the month following termination -> end of month following termination
last day of employment -> day of termination
</GROUND_RULES>

Termination Provisions Q&A:
<CONTEXT>
{{DR_MTerminationProvisionQA}}
</CONTEXT>

<QUESTIONS>
Return the termination provision in the required format. <Answer/Null>
</QUESTIONS>

<EXAMPLES>
Coverage terminates end of month of employment termination
Med/Vis: Coverage terminates end of month following termination
Dtl: Coverage terminates day of termination
Med/Vis/Rx: Coverage terminates end of month following termination
Null
</EXAMPLES>

<GROUND_RULES>
Use ONLY explicit text in the provided context. No assumptions.
Use ONLY these status values: Present or Not found.
If a topic is Present, include 1 verbatim supporting snippet.
If Not found, output Language: Null.
Do NOT rewrite the snippet; copy verbatim only.

TRUNCATION RULE:
- If the best supporting language is longer than ~25 words, truncate it and end with "..."
- If not truncated, do not add "..."
</GROUND_RULES>

<CONTEXT>
{{DR_MExclusionLimitationQA}}
</CONTEXT>

<QUESTIONS>
Produce the Exclusions & Limitations checklist in the required format. <Answer>
</QUESTIONS>

<OUTPUT_FORMAT>
Overall Exclusions & Limitations Language: <Present/Not found>
Language: "<snippet/Null>"

Mental Health / Substance Use Disorder: <Present/Not found>
Language: "<snippet/Null>"

Gene Therapy / Orphan Drugs: <Present/Not found>
Language: "<snippet/Null>"

Foreign Travel / Abroad: <Present/Not found>
Language: "<snippet/Null>"

Crime/Felony/Illegal Acts Injury: <Present/Not found>
Language: "<snippet/Null>"

Weight Loss / Weight Loss Drugs: <Present/Not found>
Language: "<snippet/Null>"
</OUTPUT_FORMAT>
